00:03:32,446 --> 00:03:35,136
On the 15th of May, in the jungle of Nool,

3
00:03:35,582 --> 00:03:38,482
in the heat of the day,
in the cool of the pool,

4
00:03:38,952 --> 00:03:41,972
he was splashing,
enjoying the jungle's great joys,

5
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:48,796
when Horton the Elephant
heard a small noise.

6
00:03:59,773 --> 00:04:00,883
-Horton!
-Horton!

7
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,881
Good morning, class. Are you ready?

8
00:04:04,211 --> 00:04:05,991
-Yeah!
-Jump on board!

9
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:08,737
Look out below!

10
00:04:09,049 --> 00:04:11,539
Tommy's on board. Katie, you there?

11
00:04:14,788 --> 00:04:16,078
Okay.

12
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:20,459
There it is.

13
00:04:20,761 --> 00:04:24,451
This is one of the jungle's most
amazing creatures, the leaf bug.

14
00:04:25,065 --> 00:04:29,165
In order to protect itself from predators,
it disguises itself as a leaf.

15
00:04:35,575 --> 00:04:38,474
This one's got quite a grip.
Come on, little buddy.

16
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:40,255
Don't be shy.

17
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:45,200
I guess I was mistaken, kids.

18
00:04:45,652 --> 00:04:48,692
There are obviously no leaf bugs
in this area. Even if...

19
00:04:49,222 --> 00:04:50,712
No, they're on me!

20
00:04:55,996 --> 00:04:57,806
I think I swallowed one!

21
00:04:58,765 --> 00:05:00,075
Tommy! Pull it out!

22
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:01,793
Uh, okay.

23
00:05:07,073 --> 00:05:09,652
Then humpfing a "humpf"
was a sour Kangaroo,

24
00:05:10,110 --> 00:05:12,770
the type who's convinced
she knows better than you.

25
00:05:13,246 --> 00:05:16,025
She made every law
and enforced every rule

26
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:19,353
as self-proclaimed
head of the jungle of Neal.

27
00:05:21,188 --> 00:05:22,798
Why can't I play with the other kids, Mom?

28
00:05:23,123 --> 00:05:24,433
How many times have I told you that

29
00:05:24,691 --> 00:05:27,561
the jungle is no place
to act like a wild animal.

30
00:05:38,772 --> 00:05:40,962
My, that Horton certainly is eccentric.

31
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:43,891
And the children are learning
so much from him.

32
00:05:44,311 --> 00:05:47,121
Learning to be a bunch
of harebrained half-wits!

33
00:05:47,747 --> 00:05:50,327
And that's why my Rudy
is pouch-schooled.

34
00:05:51,084 --> 00:05:53,484
So while Kangaree stood there,
-
sneering a sneer...

35
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,620
Horton, that was the best time
I've ever had in my life!

36
00:05:55,956 --> 00:05:56,416
What are you gonna show us next?

37
00:05:57,691 --> 00:06:01,061
..once again, the speck floated
right by Horton's ear.

38
00:06:02,963 --> 00:06:05,513
Then he heard it again,
just a very faint yelp,

39
00:06:05,966 --> 00:06:08,136
as if some tiny person
were calling for help.

40
00:06:12,172 --> 00:06:13,372
And you know what he thought?

41
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:15,250
Why, he thought that
there must be someone

42
00:06:15,542 --> 00:06:18,092
on top of that small speck of dust!

43
00:06:18,511 --> 00:06:20,561
Or even a family, it just might be so,

44
00:06:20,947 --> 00:06:23,347
a family with children
just starting to grow.

45
00:06:26,653 --> 00:06:27,643
I want to live!

46
00:06:30,490 --> 00:06:32,890
I gotta go. Katie, you're in charge!

47
00:06:37,497 --> 00:06:38,637
Wait!

48
00:06:38,865 --> 00:06:40,705
-Come back!
-Watch it!

49
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:08,707
One more! One more! One more!

50
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:18,027
-l hear someone coming!
-Give me those!

51
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:21,389
-Wait!
-Sound the alarm!

52
00:07:25,478 --> 00:07:27,528
Excuse me. Pardon my stampede!

53
00:07:28,581 --> 00:07:31,651
Sorry, Wickershams! I promise
I'm gonna clean all this up later!

54
00:07:32,185 --> 00:07:33,555
Bring the ammo!

55
00:07:42,362 --> 00:07:44,992
I love the smell of bananas in the morning.

56
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:48,346
Banana in the hole!

57
00:07:49,336 --> 00:07:51,556
Come on, guys! We're all mammals!

58
00:07:54,274 --> 00:07:57,734
I feel the diplomatic process
is beginning to break down.

59
00:08:00,447 --> 00:08:02,287
There you are! I got you!

60
00:08:07,187 --> 00:08:08,357
Hi, kids!

61
00:08:17,464 --> 00:08:18,484
Wow.

62
00:08:22,602 --> 00:08:23,652
There.

63
00:08:24,738 --> 00:08:26,168
Now you're safe.

64
00:08:27,407 --> 00:08:30,477
I know I heard you say something.
I just know it.

65
00:08:32,746 --> 00:08:34,086
Where are you?

66
00:08:42,155 --> 00:08:43,115
Horton!

67
00:08:43,323 --> 00:08:44,433
Sorry!

68
00:08:45,725 --> 00:08:50,035
I just... There was this speck,
and it called out for help.

69
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:53,010
-And I was...
-The speck called out for help?

70
00:08:53,433 --> 00:08:56,393
Well, not the speck.
I mean, that's ridiculous.

71
00:08:58,538 --> 00:09:01,528
Is that what you thought I meant?
No, the speck can't call out for help.

72
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:03,972
Come on, get real.

73
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:09,112
No, there's a tiny person on that speck
that needs my help.

74
00:09:10,283 --> 00:09:13,323
Absurd. There aren't people that small!

75
00:09:13,987 --> 00:09:16,036
Well, maybe they aren't small.

76
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:18,803
-Maybe we're big.
-Horton.

77
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:23,079
No, really, think about it.
What if there was someone way out there

78
00:09:24,297 --> 00:09:26,317
looking down on our world right now?

79
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:28,686
And to them, we're the specks.

80
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:30,755
And then, maybe someone else
will come along and say,

81
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:33,181
“Oh, there can't be people that small",
and the first guy would say,

82
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:34,502
“Are you calling me a liar?”

83
00:09:34,741 --> 00:09:37,111
And the second guy would say,
“If the shoe fits, wear it!"

84
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:39,680
And now the fists are flying,
and the first guy picks up a brick,

85
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:42,450
and you might want to zip up the pouch
for this next part.

86
00:09:42,849 --> 00:09:44,459
“All right, fat boy,
you want some of this..."

87
00:09:44,784 --> 00:09:45,834
-Horton!
-What?

88
00:09:46,086 --> 00:09:48,166
There is nothing on that speck.

89
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:51,566
-But I heard.
-Did you?

90
00:09:51,858 --> 00:09:53,907
Really? Oh, my.

91
00:09:54,627 --> 00:09:56,967
Then how come I don't hear anything?

92
00:09:58,198 --> 00:09:59,367
Well...

93
00:10:00,633 --> 00:10:04,413
If you can't see, hear or feel something,

94
00:10:05,004 --> 00:10:06,494
it doesn't exist.

95
00:10:06,806 --> 00:10:09,496
And believing in tiny, imaginary people

96
00:10:09,976 --> 00:10:13,666
is just not something we do or tolerate,

97
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:16,030
here in the jungle of Nool.

98
00:10:16,349 --> 00:10:20,269
Really? Because I bet if I really tried,
I could find somebody who'd believe

99
00:10:20,887 --> 00:10:22,406
-what I've been saying.
-You will do nothing of the sort.

100
00:10:22,689 --> 00:10:27,169
You will not breathe a word of this lie
to anyone else, especially the children.

101
00:10:27,861 --> 00:10:31,231
I do not want you poisoning their minds
with this nonsense.

102
00:10:32,665 --> 00:10:34,885
Our community has standards, Horton.

103
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:38,901
If you want to remain a part of it,
l recommend you follow them.

104
00:10:41,007 --> 00:10:42,467
Have a nice day.

105
00:10:46,346 --> 00:10:49,306
All right, then,
I'll take that under advisement.

106
00:10:49,816 --> 00:10:51,276
Certainly appreciate your input.

107
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:57,144
I don't understand. I know I heard you.

108
00:10:57,724 --> 00:11:00,184
It was as plain as the nose on my face.

109
00:11:00,960 --> 00:11:03,590
That's it. Maybe you can't hear me.

110
00:11:04,697 --> 00:11:08,537
Of course! Your ears must be tiny.
I need to speak up.

111
00:11:11,471 --> 00:11:14,401
Hello!

112
00:11:14,874 --> 00:11:17,214
Now some people out there,
l think l know whe,

113
00:11:17,644 --> 00:11:20,304
may find they agree
with that sour Kangaroo.

114
00:11:21,347 --> 00:11:24,247
"There can't really be people
as small as a mite."

115
00:11:24,717 --> 00:11:28,937
Well, there can, and there are,
because Horton was right.

116
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,673
Hello!

117
00:11:44,837 --> 00:11:47,207
That single "hello" traveled
all the way down

118
00:11:47,607 --> 00:11:51,327
to the speck, through the clouds,
until it found a small town.

119
00:11:52,512 --> 00:11:55,291
A town known as Whoville,
for there lived the Whos,

120
00:11:55,748 --> 00:11:58,678
feeling happy and safe,
knowing only good news,

121
00:11:59,185 --> 00:12:02,285
unaware that their world
was a speck ona clover,

122
00:12:02,789 --> 00:12:05,479
unaware that the sweet life
they knew might be over.

123
00:12:05,925 --> 00:12:07,234
-Over!
-Under!

124
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:12,890
The Mayor of Whoville,
aman named McDedd,

125
00:12:13,366 --> 00:12:16,526
was devoted and fair and a little bit odd.

126
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:37,157
The Mayor and his wife,
they had children to spare,

127
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:40,680
96 daughters, some here and some there.

128
00:12:42,028 --> 00:12:45,398
96 girls to love, 96 girls to teach,

129
00:12:47,066 --> 00:12:49,846
but the Mayor had only
a few seconds for each.

130
00:12:51,204 --> 00:12:53,784
Daddy, I got better than best
on my Who-story test.

131
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:56,110
Who-story. l remember it well.

132
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:57,782
That's one of my girls.

133
00:12:58,077 --> 00:13:00,887
-Hildy's been using my hairbrush!
-Holly's been using my hairbrush!

134
00:13:01,381 --> 00:13:02,841
Look! Over there!

135
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:05,457
There. All better.

136
00:13:05,752 --> 00:13:09,031
Can I please have a Who-phone, Dad?
Everyone else in my class has one.

137
00:13:09,589 --> 00:13:11,229
Oh, really? Everyone?

138
00:13:14,661 --> 00:13:15,950
I will think about it.

139
00:13:16,229 --> 00:13:18,069
Daddy, look! Daddy, look!

140
00:13:23,169 --> 00:13:24,129
Toof.

141
00:13:24,337 --> 00:13:26,087
It's a "T-H", sweetheart. It's "tooth."

142
00:13:26,839 --> 00:13:29,029
In Whoville tradition, unlike yours or mine,

143
00:13:29,442 --> 00:13:31,812
the Mayor's oldest is next
in the Mayoral line.

144
00:13:32,245 --> 00:13:34,355
And whe was the oldest?
To lead and stand tall?

145
00:13:34,747 --> 00:13:37,526
lt was JoJo, his son,
the smallest Whe of all.

146
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:42,494
So, JoJo, what's shaking?
What's happening? What's the word?

147
00:13:44,023 --> 00:13:46,333
Now, to you or to me, it's abundantly clear

148
00:13:46,759 --> 00:13:49,449
that JoJo did not want his father’s career.

149
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:53,260
But the Mayor pressed forward,
completely deluded,

150
00:13:54,867 --> 00:13:57,857
while JoJo just sat there in silence
and broeded.

151
00:14:01,874 --> 00:14:03,334
Oh, JoJo!

152
00:14:04,944 --> 00:14:06,723
-Hey, why does he get more time?
-That's not fair.

153
00:14:08,047 --> 00:14:09,307
Son! Hey!

154
00:14:09,549 --> 00:14:10,858
And why didn't he speak?

155
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:15,340
Well, 1 think that the lad was afraid
if he did, he might let down his dad.

156
00:14:16,255 --> 00:14:17,955
You know what's awesome?

157
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:19,931
This is awesome.

158
00:14:20,259 --> 00:14:24,239
Just look at the men and women
hanging on these walls.

159
00:14:25,131 --> 00:14:30,111
You, my boy, are part of a family legacy
that spans centuries.

160
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:35,471
You know what?
Your grandfather was Mayor of Whoville,

161
00:14:37,343 --> 00:14:41,183
and your great-grandmother, that's right,

162
00:14:42,181 --> 00:14:44,461
all the way down to your

163
00:14:46,152 --> 00:14:49,962
great-great-great-great-not-so-great-

164
00:14:50,556 --> 00:14:54,366
great-great-great-great-great-great-
great-great-great-great-

165
00:14:57,029 --> 00:14:58,319
grandfather.

166
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,853
Someday I hope to join them.

167
00:15:04,036 --> 00:15:05,616
Be one of the greats.

168
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:09,824
I tell you, JoJo, there is nothing
like being Mayor.

169
00:15:10,476 --> 00:15:13,876
I get to sign resolutions,
approve ordinances, submit budgets,

170
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:18,604
and in the Edible Parade, I'm the one
sitting on top of the giant meatball.

171
00:15:21,154 --> 00:15:24,254
Someday, that can be you, too, JoJo.

172
00:15:25,224 --> 00:15:29,324
Someday you'll be the one wearing
the Mayoral Crest.

173
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,490
You just... You just need to...

174
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:37,939
You know what I mean?

175
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:40,855
Okay. Good chat.

176
00:15:41,874 --> 00:15:45,064
I'm glad that we had this talk

177
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:50,239
that I'm continuing now by myself. Good.

178
00:15:58,024 --> 00:16:00,074
There. That ought to be comfy.

179
00:16:04,263 --> 00:16:08,163
Nothing wrong with this, Morton.
Nothing wrong with this.

180
00:16:10,403 --> 00:16:13,273
Just you, me and the speck,
shooting the breeze.

181
00:16:14,040 --> 00:16:17,849
We're a club. We're a group.
We can take a vote on the issues.

182
00:16:18,444 --> 00:16:22,014
We can be a secret society that controls
the balance of power in the world.

183
00:16:22,582 --> 00:16:23,872
-Horton.
-And no one else can join,

184
00:16:24,116 --> 00:16:26,106
unless they wear funny hats.

185
00:16:28,621 --> 00:16:30,141
Listen, Horton!

186
00:16:30,423 --> 00:16:32,643
The Chair recognizes Brother Morton.

187
00:16:33,059 --> 00:16:36,159
lam really happy you found
this speck and all,

188
00:16:37,897 --> 00:16:41,177
but you might want to think
about keeping it to yourself.

189
00:16:42,235 --> 00:16:43,435
What? Why?

190
00:16:44,637 --> 00:16:47,827
Well, you're talking to a clover.
That doesn't look good.

191
00:16:50,810 --> 00:16:52,560
You know what doesn't look good?

192
00:16:52,912 --> 00:16:55,722
You talking about the speck
like the speck isn't even there.

193
00:16:56,215 --> 00:16:58,795
The speck never said anything bad
about you.

194
00:16:59,252 --> 00:17:01,942
But, hey! Good luck
with your illusion of superiority.

195
00:17:02,421 --> 00:17:06,401
You know, the speck can think anything
it wants about me. It's a speck.

196
00:17:07,894 --> 00:17:09,944
I see what's going on here.

197
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:14,457
Morton, no matter how tight
the speck and I get,

198
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,580
the speck could never replace you.

199
00:17:18,237 --> 00:17:21,077
I'm only sad that I would have
to explain that, at this point.

200
00:17:21,574 --> 00:17:24,854
Well, that's awesome, Horton.
That really helps.

201
00:17:25,744 --> 00:17:28,405
Just try to keep this to yourself.

202
00:17:29,081 --> 00:17:31,011
I'll see you later. Try.

203
00:17:36,856 --> 00:17:38,586
Hey, Horton! What you got there?

204
00:17:38,925 --> 00:17:40,264
What? Nothing!

205
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:42,729
We're not doing anything.

206
00:17:43,963 --> 00:17:46,072
-We're totally alone.
-Who's "we"?

207
00:17:46,465 --> 00:17:48,544
“We"? What? "We"? Did I say that?
I just... Oh.

208
00:17:48,935 --> 00:17:50,425
No, I would never say that,
because that would imply that

209
00:17:50,703 --> 00:17:52,953
I was with someone, and not alone.

210
00:17:59,645 --> 00:18:01,985
Okay, seriously, you can't tell anybody.
I mean it.

211
00:18:02,415 --> 00:18:05,845
If anybody finds out about this,
it could be very, very bad.

212
00:18:07,186 --> 00:18:08,735
I'm not sure why.

213
00:18:09,689 --> 00:18:10,919
We won't tell anyone.

214
00:18:11,157 --> 00:18:14,407
And if we do,
we'll tell them not to tell anyone.

215
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:16,603
Perfect!

216
00:18:17,029 --> 00:18:18,339
Okay, I'm taking a bath, right,

217
00:18:18,631 --> 00:18:20,441
‘cause my skin gets kind of dry
and a little bit ashy.

218
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:23,200
While Horton came clean about
the speck that he'd found

219
00:18:23,636 --> 00:18:25,566
and how he had saved it
when it nearly drowned,

220
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:27,488
the Mayor set off on his morning commute

221
00:18:27,807 --> 00:18:30,647
and noticed things weren't quite
the same on his route.

222
00:18:31,143 --> 00:18:35,013
But please don't blame Horton, for he
didn't know that a small bump above...

223
00:18:35,648 --> 00:18:37,398
..and I dove in the water like this!

224
00:18:39,218 --> 00:18:41,118
.. was a big bump below.

225
00:18:43,322 --> 00:18:44,901
Hey, Joe, don't work too hard.

226
00:18:45,191 --> 00:18:48,061
These luxury condos,
they don't build themselves.

227
00:18:52,231 --> 00:18:55,161
Hey, look at that!
I guess they do build themselves.

228
00:18:55,668 --> 00:18:57,777
Okay, that happened.

229
00:19:01,574 --> 00:19:04,644
Now, the Mayor knew it was his job
to convey the unusual things

230
00:19:05,177 --> 00:19:08,276
that he'd noticed that day,
but there was one problem.

231
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:10,424
Though his will was strong...

232
00:19:10,716 --> 00:19:12,416
-You're late.
-Thank you, Miss Yelp.

233
00:19:12,918 --> 00:19:15,848
. nothing in Whoeville
had ever gone wrong.

234
00:19:16,355 --> 00:19:19,285
We have all that we need.
We need all that we've got.

235
00:19:19,759 --> 00:19:23,419
We like it in Whoville. We like it a lot!

236
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:27,430
We're all very busy with
the Who-Centennial coming up,

237
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,370
so let's bring this meeting to order.

238
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:34,480
Mr. Mayor, I presume you
have some good news for us.

239
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:37,650
Well, it's news.

240
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:41,990
I don't know if we need to go labeling it
“good" or "bad" or anything like that.

241
00:19:42,615 --> 00:19:47,215
The thing is, I have noticed
some odd goings-on in Whoville lately.

242
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,500
Good "odd goings-on"?

243
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:53,272
Well, you know, tremors,
clouds swirling in the sky.

244
00:19:53,793 --> 00:19:55,372
And it seems to me, just to be safe,

245
00:19:55,695 --> 00:19:58,245
we might want to consider
postponing the Who-Centennial.

246
00:19:58,698 --> 00:20:00,038
Consider what?

247
00:20:00,766 --> 00:20:01,936
Postponing the Who-Centennial.

248
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:05,212
What? Speak up, man!

249
00:20:06,706 --> 00:20:09,285
Postponing the Who-Centennial! All right?

250
00:20:30,429 --> 00:20:34,709
We are about to celebrate 100 years
of Whoville happiness and harmony,

251
00:20:35,401 --> 00:20:37,331
and you want to postpone the celebration?

252
00:20:37,670 --> 00:20:39,070
Well, what if Whoville’s not safe?

253
00:20:39,338 --> 00:20:41,968
Nothing ever goes wrong in Whoville,

254
00:20:42,441 --> 00:20:46,391
never has and never will,
you blathering boob!

255
00:20:52,184 --> 00:20:55,114
The Who-Centennial will proceed
as planned!

256
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:58,518
The Mayor was merely being an idiot.

257
00:20:58,958 --> 00:21:01,648
It will be all smiles from now on.

258
00:21:05,798 --> 00:21:06,698
That hurt!

259
00:21:08,534 --> 00:21:10,964
Girl, got 15,000 friends already.

260
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:13,040
What? What do you mean,
it don't look like me?

261
00:21:13,339 --> 00:21:17,408
That looks just like me 10 years ago.
Wait a minute. Hold on for a second.

262
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:24,941
Treats me like an idiot. 1 am not an idiot.

263
00:21:27,686 --> 00:21:29,466
Do I look like an idiot?

264
00:21:30,723 --> 00:21:33,853
-You don't want me to answer that.
-l am not an idiot.

265
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:38,080
Has the nerve to call me a boob?
I would never call somebody a boob.

266
00:21:38,631 --> 00:21:40,441
He's a boob! Look at you.

267
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,320
Yuck!

268
00:21:42,835 --> 00:21:44,355
Look at your face.

269
00:21:44,904 --> 00:21:48,414
And I bet you don't look so good
with a stapler in your head!

270
00:21:58,918 --> 00:22:00,588
Whoa! Whoa.

271
00:22:04,490 --> 00:22:06,920
-Thank you, Miss Yelp.
-You're welcome.

272
00:22:08,861 --> 00:22:09,791
Hello?

273
00:22:10,062 --> 00:22:13,371
Who said that? Back off! I'll punch you!

274
00:22:23,576 --> 00:22:24,536
Hello?

275
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:28,900
Hello.

276
00:22:36,322 --> 00:22:37,581
Who's there?

277
00:22:38,357 --> 00:22:39,257
This is the Mayor.

278
00:22:40,092 --> 00:22:41,962
The Mayor? The Mayor!

279
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:44,898
I'm talking to the Mayor!

280
00:22:46,866 --> 00:22:49,996
I knew it. I knew it. I knew it.
I knew there was life on this speck.

281
00:22:50,736 --> 00:22:52,516
“This speck"? What speck?

282
00:22:53,272 --> 00:22:57,081
Well, I don't exactly know
how to tell you this, but...

283
00:22:58,677 --> 00:23:00,867
You're living on a speck.

284
00:23:01,247 --> 00:23:05,317
Well, l hate to disagree with you,
O voice from the drainpipe,

285
00:23:05,951 --> 00:23:07,701
but I live in Whoville.

286
00:23:08,354 --> 00:23:10,284
Well, then, Whoville's a speck.

287
00:23:10,623 --> 00:23:11,553
Right.

288
00:23:11,757 --> 00:23:14,247
Okay, seriously, who is this?

289
00:23:15,194 --> 00:23:16,364
Is this Burt from accounting?

290
00:23:17,630 --> 00:23:20,210
No. This is Horton. I'm an elephant.

291
00:23:20,766 --> 00:23:23,576
Okay, “Horton.”

292
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:26,089
Fake name. Where are you?

293
00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:31,128
Well, from where you're standing,
f guess I'm in the sky.

294
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:33,781
Compared to you, I'm enormous.

295
00:23:34,046 --> 00:23:36,296
Which is saying something,
because I've slimmed down quite a bit.

296
00:23:36,715 --> 00:23:37,794
I swim.

297
00:23:38,484 --> 00:23:42,204
Your whole world fits on a flower
in my world.

298
00:23:42,988 --> 00:23:45,418
Oh, man, this is even pushing it
for you, Burt.

299
00:23:45,991 --> 00:23:48,601
Don't believe me? Watch what happens
when I put you in the shade.

300
00:23:49,061 --> 00:23:51,021
This is absolutely impossible...

301
00:23:51,397 --> 00:23:52,417
Dark.

302
00:23:53,565 --> 00:23:54,495
Light.

303
00:23:55,134 --> 00:23:56,154
Dark.

304
00:23:56,835 --> 00:23:59,875
Light. Dark, light, dark, light,
dark, light, dark.

305
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,520
Light!

306
00:24:03,509 --> 00:24:04,469
Don't you see?

307
00:24:05,311 --> 00:24:08,941
We're in the middle of some kind of
- -
amazing cosmic convergence.

308
00:24:10,082 --> 00:24:13,802
Two vastly different worlds,
miraculously crossing paths!

309
00:24:14,586 --> 00:24:16,806
Mine, colossal! Yours, miniscule.

310
00:24:17,189 --> 00:24:19,649
Yet somehow we've managed
to make contact.

311
00:24:20,192 --> 00:24:22,822
if you think about it, it's pretty amazing.

312
00:24:26,799 --> 00:24:27,999
Is everything okay down there?

313
00:24:30,636 --> 00:24:34,206
I don't know. You tell me.
You're the one holding the speck.

314
00:24:35,674 --> 00:24:37,724
I'm the one holding the speck.

315
00:24:38,477 --> 00:24:39,787
I'm the one holding the speck.

316
00:24:40,546 --> 00:24:42,446
Don't you worry, Mr. Mayor.

317
00:24:44,616 --> 00:24:45,436
Hold, please!

318
00:24:48,187 --> 00:24:50,937
What did all of this mean?
The Mayor hadn't a clue.

319
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:56,140
So he ran to the office of Dr. Larue,
the brainiest brain on the staff at Whe U.

320
00:24:56,862 --> 00:24:58,032
Dr. Larue!

321
00:25:00,032 --> 00:25:01,611
This is crazy.

322
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:03,270
Mr. Mayor.

323
00:25:04,737 --> 00:25:06,167
How may I be of assistance?

324
00:25:06,472 --> 00:25:08,662
I don't know. Hey, you know,
I was just wondering

325
00:25:09,041 --> 00:25:13,231
if our world were, say, a tiny speck
floating through space,

326
00:25:13,879 --> 00:25:14,779
how would we know?

327
00:25:15,014 --> 00:25:16,533
Well, why would you ask
something like that?

328
00:25:16,849 --> 00:25:19,658
No reason. No reason at all.
I don't even remember.

329
00:25:20,152 --> 00:25:21,962
Yes, 1 do. You know what?

330
00:25:22,321 --> 00:25:24,021
Some guy was talking to me.

331
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:26,816
Not an elephant in the sky.
A guy on the ground.

332
00:25:27,226 --> 00:25:29,306
There would be several ramifications.

333
00:25:29,695 --> 00:25:31,304
Good ramifications?

334
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:33,734
A tiny speck?

335
00:25:34,867 --> 00:25:36,357
Yeah. Tiny speck.

336
00:25:36,668 --> 00:25:38,158
Floating around.

337
00:25:39,271 --> 00:25:44,101
Well, we'd have inexplicable tremors,
dramatic changes in the weather,

338
00:25:45,444 --> 00:25:48,813
and if we didn't eventually achieve
some sort of stability,

339
00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:52,451
our world would be destroyed!

340
00:25:53,419 --> 00:25:56,349
Destroyed? Destroyed. Oh, destroyed.

341
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:03,610
Horton!

342
00:26:03,962 --> 00:26:06,102
No, this is Benny.

343
00:26:07,132 --> 00:26:09,302
Horton is busy right now.

344
00:26:10,135 --> 00:26:11,425
No. I'm joking.

345
00:26:11,870 --> 00:26:13,040
That's me.

346
00:26:13,906 --> 00:26:15,196
We're doomed.

347
00:26:15,441 --> 00:26:19,071
Listen, Horton, turns out
I need your help a little bit.

348
00:26:19,645 --> 00:26:21,665
Apparently, if that speck
keeps moving around,

349
00:26:22,047 --> 00:26:24,417
our whole world could be obliterated.

350
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:29,820
Sol need you to find us Whos
a safer, more stable home,

351
00:26:30,556 --> 00:26:31,486
and fast.

352
00:26:32,157 --> 00:26:34,496
No problem, Mr. Mayor. Let's see...

353
00:26:37,229 --> 00:26:39,569
Wow, that's a nice view.

354
00:26:42,935 --> 00:26:44,304
Hello. Is everything okay?

355
00:26:54,413 --> 00:26:55,313
What's going on up there?

356
00:27:09,862 --> 00:27:12,962
This entire jungle is a house of death!

357
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:16,349
Oh, wait. There's a good spot.

358
00:27:16,969 --> 00:27:19,839
And it's then Horten saw
at the top of Mount Nool,

359
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:23,175
a small cave that looked peaceful
and quiet and coal,

360
00:27:23,642 --> 00:27:26,362
where a sunflower grew proud and tall
from the ground.

361
00:27:26,812 --> 00:27:30,472
There, he knew every Whe would be safe,
would be sound.

362
00:27:31,083 --> 00:27:34,043
I found it, Mayor. The perfect place.

363
00:27:35,420 --> 00:27:36,500
Right up there,

364
00:27:37,289 --> 00:27:39,689
-on the top of Mount Neal.
-Mr. Mayor?

365
00:27:40,259 --> 00:27:41,809
l wish you could...

366
00:27:42,828 --> 00:27:43,848
Shiny.

367
00:27:45,797 --> 00:27:47,727
The Who-Centennial Committee
is waiting for you

368
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:50,879
to look over the giant meatball
for the Edible Parade.

369
00:27:51,336 --> 00:27:53,826
And then you're due at the dentist
for your Who-root canal.

370
00:27:54,273 --> 00:27:57,963
You know, sticking "Who" in front
of everything doesn't make it hurt less.

371
00:27:58,544 --> 00:28:00,244
Just wastes time!

372
00:28:00,546 --> 00:28:02,156
I don't want to go.

373
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:05,369
Listen, Horton, I've gotta go.

374
00:28:05,617 --> 00:28:07,547
Apparently, there's a problem
with the giant meatball.

375
00:28:08,153 --> 00:28:13,013
You just take care of that meatball, sir,
and leave the freaking out to me.

376
00:28:13,792 --> 00:28:16,341
So then Horton began
his long, perilous trek,

377
00:28:16,795 --> 00:28:19,665
determined to save the small world
on the speck.

378
00:28:20,999 --> 00:28:23,249
Horton was faithful and stalwart and kind.

379
00:28:23,669 --> 00:28:24,959
I got you.

380
00:28:25,204 --> 00:28:26,904
He was a brave here...

381
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:28,106
I'll protect you!

382
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:29,540
.at least in his mind.

383
00:28:29,808 --> 00:28:32,088
We must become invisible. Travel silently.

384
00:28:32,511 --> 00:28:35,001
For there are forces
that would seek to destroy us.

385
00:28:41,853 --> 00:28:44,403
So you think you can sneak up
on me, huh?

386
00:28:46,525 --> 00:28:49,485
It is clear that you are no match
for my technique.

387
00:28:52,197 --> 00:28:56,177
I see you have mastered the way of the
snapping branch. Watch me tumble!

388
00:28:58,370 --> 00:28:59,570
Morton Mouse, go!

389
00:28:59,838 --> 00:29:02,418
You are fast, Horton,
but the Kangaroo has monkeys.

390
00:29:02,874 --> 00:29:06,214
I will make monkeys of these monkeys.
It is their destiny.

391
00:29:06,878 --> 00:29:08,187
More clover!

392
00:29:10,549 --> 00:29:12,769
Horton is the greatest hero of them all!

393
00:29:13,185 --> 00:29:14,115
-Horton!
-Morton!

394
00:29:14,353 --> 00:29:15,253
Go!

395
00:29:17,756 --> 00:29:19,746
But Mount Nool is that way.

396
00:29:21,093 --> 00:29:24,023
To the top of Mount Nool!
As fast as lightning! Away, I go.

397
00:29:26,732 --> 00:29:28,341
Sorry, little fellow.

398
00:29:29,034 --> 00:29:31,844
You'll be fine. Just think healing thoughts.

399
00:29:35,941 --> 00:29:38,521
-Horton! Look!
-Horton! Look, look, look!

400
00:29:40,279 --> 00:29:42,619
We've all got our own clovers
with worlds on them!

401
00:29:43,048 --> 00:29:44,098
Yeah.

402
00:29:46,385 --> 00:29:48,665
In my world, everyone's a pony,

403
00:29:49,087 --> 00:29:51,927
and they all eat rainbows
and poop butterflies.

404
00:29:54,159 --> 00:29:56,119
That's beautiful, Katie.

405
00:30:00,599 --> 00:30:02,379
In a really weird way.

406
00:30:02,734 --> 00:30:05,254
My world is called Jessica-land,
and everyone worships Queen Jessica

407
00:30:05,671 --> 00:30:07,221
because Jessica is so beautiful.

408
00:30:07,506 --> 00:30:09,996
Jessica, that was awesome.

409
00:30:15,347 --> 00:30:16,427
-Rudy!
-Mom, be careful!

410
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:17,848
My best friend Thidwick lives on that.

411
00:30:18,116 --> 00:30:21,656
Rudy, no one lives on this.
It's not possible.

412
00:30:22,521 --> 00:30:24,041
That Horton is a menace.

413
00:30:24,323 --> 00:30:26,253
Mom, Mom! Please, you're so weird.
Don't do this to me.

414
00:30:26,625 --> 00:30:27,965
Honey, go to your room.

415
00:30:28,260 --> 00:30:29,370
Horton!

416
00:30:32,664 --> 00:30:34,154
It's good!

417
00:30:34,466 --> 00:30:36,075
What do you think you're doing?

418
00:30:36,368 --> 00:30:37,737
You guys with worlds are in trouble!

419
00:30:38,003 --> 00:30:41,693
-Have you forgotten what we discussed?
-Oh, no. I'm an elephant,

420
00:30:42,307 --> 00:30:44,357
and elephants never forget.
It's a curse, really.

421
00:30:44,710 --> 00:30:46,380
l remember I was on my head,
and you said “Humpf,"

422
00:30:46,678 --> 00:30:48,108
and I looked up, and you said,
“What are you doing?"

423
00:30:48,380 --> 00:30:49,490
And I said the thing about the speck.

424
00:30:49,715 --> 00:30:51,554
Then you pulled my ears
and you poked me in the forehead...

425
00:30:51,883 --> 00:30:53,633
-Horton!
-Well, you did.

426
00:30:53,985 --> 00:30:56,675
Give me that clover, Horton. Now!

427
00:30:58,523 --> 00:30:59,513
No.

428
00:31:03,161 --> 00:31:04,151
No?

429
00:31:05,564 --> 00:31:06,644
Yeah.

430
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:09,675
Are you sure you want to fight
this fight, Horton?

431
00:31:10,168 --> 00:31:14,267
Because I promise you
it will get very ugly, very fast.

432
00:31:14,906 --> 00:31:17,046
And you need to ask yourself,

433
00:31:17,409 --> 00:31:20,429
“Dol really want
