00:37:36,321 --> 00:37:37,841
Hey, hon,

496
00:37:40,558 --> 00:37:43,928
did you ever get the feeling
that you were being watched?

497
00:37:45,830 --> 00:37:48,900
Yeah, sure. I suppose.

498
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:53,120
And then you get the feeling that
maybe that thing watching you is

499
00:37:55,073 --> 00:37:56,623
a giant elephant?

500
00:37:57,709 --> 00:38:00,319
And you know how
you get that weird feeling

501
00:38:00,745 --> 00:38:03,375
that your world is actually a tiny speck?

502
00:38:03,848 --> 00:38:09,328
And that the elephant that I talked about
earlier is carrying it around on a flower.

503
00:38:10,188 --> 00:38:13,908
And you realize that if you tell anybody,
they'd think you were crazy.

504
00:38:14,526 --> 00:38:18,625
But you still feel a responsibility
to keep everyone safe.

505
00:38:19,731 --> 00:38:21,461
You know that feeling?

506
00:38:22,734 --> 00:38:25,194
You know, I'm gonna have to say no.

507
00:38:25,603 --> 00:38:27,473
Do you know that feeling?

508
00:38:30,942 --> 00:38:31,932
No.

509
00:38:33,678 --> 00:38:37,578
Yawn. Wow. I am beat.
Time to hit the hay, I guess.

510
00:38:38,416 --> 00:38:41,346
Sweetheart, I know
you're under a lot of stress,

511
00:38:42,187 --> 00:38:46,167
and if you're seeing elephants
and flowers, then fine.

512
00:38:46,791 --> 00:38:49,511
Just don't tell anyone else
that story, okay?

513
00:38:49,961 --> 00:38:52,591
And remember,
it's not the end of the world.

514
00:38:55,300 --> 00:38:56,910
“The end of the world.”

515
00:38:58,303 --> 00:39:01,022
Horton to Mayor. Horton to Mayor.
Come in, Mayor. Over.

516
00:39:03,741 --> 00:39:04,821
Horton?

517
00:39:06,578 --> 00:39:08,158
I get terrible reception here.

518
00:39:08,580 --> 00:39:11,920
How about this?
If l get up real close, can you read me?

519
00:39:15,587 --> 00:39:17,397
Yep! Roger that.

520
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:19,719
Are we at that safe place yet?

521
00:39:20,158 --> 00:39:23,228
Almost. I'm pretty sure
the worst part's over.

522
00:39:23,761 --> 00:39:25,341
This is your elephant speaking.

523
00:39:25,630 --> 00:39:28,730
Just sit back, enjoy the ride, and
we'll have you to Mount Nool in no time.

524
00:39:29,267 --> 00:39:30,997
No, you can't have ice cream for breakfast.

525
00:39:31,302 --> 00:39:32,202
-Please.
-Please.

526
00:39:32,437 --> 00:39:33,487
Who's that?

527
00:39:33,738 --> 00:39:35,048
Is there someone else there?

528
00:39:35,306 --> 00:39:37,236
Well, that's my wife and kids.

529
00:39:37,609 --> 00:39:38,949
You have a family.

530
00:39:39,444 --> 00:39:44,774
I do, indeed. A beautiful wife,
96 daughters, and one son.

531
00:39:45,783 --> 00:39:47,123
Oh, busy guy.

532
00:39:47,785 --> 00:39:49,975
And we all share one bathroom.
You know how that is.

533
00:39:50,755 --> 00:39:52,565
Yeah. Don't I know it.

534
00:39:53,791 --> 00:39:54,961
Bathroom?

535
00:39:55,460 --> 00:39:56,540
-Ned!
-What?

536
00:39:56,794 --> 00:39:59,984
Sweetheart, you know
you're on the roof, right?

537
00:40:00,498 --> 00:40:01,458
-Please, Mom.
-What's that?

538
00:40:01,666 --> 00:40:03,746
No, you need to go to bed.
Daddy's having a breakdown.

539
00:40:04,135 --> 00:40:06,035
Ned, what are you up to now?

540
00:40:06,371 --> 00:40:09,301
I was just about to put the kids to bed
when I got off the roof.

541
00:40:09,807 --> 00:40:12,296
And that's what happened. Right.

542
00:40:29,127 --> 00:40:30,797
-Daddy?
-Yes.

543
00:40:31,129 --> 00:40:33,499
-Can I have a glass of water?
-Of course.

544
00:40:33,898 --> 00:40:35,298
-Me, too.
-Me, three.

545
00:40:38,236 --> 00:40:39,196
Me, 28.

546
00:40:39,404 --> 00:40:40,424
Okay.

547
00:40:46,077 --> 00:40:47,247
Hey, JoJo!

548
00:40:48,646 --> 00:40:52,246
A lot of liquid. A lot of liquid.
Just the person I wanted to see.

549
00:40:52,850 --> 00:40:57,130
Yeah, I realize that we have not
been seeing eye-to-eye lately,

550
00:40:57,822 --> 00:40:59,522
and most of it is my fault.

551
00:40:59,857 --> 00:41:00,757
It's true.

552
00:41:00,992 --> 00:41:02,542
You know what I've been trying to do?

553
00:41:02,860 --> 00:41:06,400
I have been trying to impose
my vision of your future on you.

554
00:41:07,532 --> 00:41:09,612
Let me make this perfectly clear.

555
00:41:10,001 --> 00:41:13,981
JoJo, you can be whatever
kind of Mayor you want to be.

556
00:41:14,639 --> 00:41:17,889
Hands-on, strong and silent,
outspoken, it's up to you.

557
00:41:18,409 --> 00:41:21,159
Well, good. I feel so much better.

558
00:41:21,646 --> 00:41:25,156
lam expecting big things from you,
young man. Big things.

559
00:41:25,717 --> 00:41:27,327
All right. Good night.

560
00:41:27,652 --> 00:41:29,352
Good stuff. Good talk.

561
00:41:44,168 --> 00:41:47,128
Then JoJo snuck out,
feeling lonely and sad,

562
00:41:47,605 --> 00:41:50,155
and tragically misunderstood by his dad.

563
00:42:06,758 --> 00:42:09,368
And where was he going
at such a late hour?

564
00:42:12,196 --> 00:42:15,006
Up te Whoville's abandoned
Star-Studying Tower,

565
00:42:16,801 --> 00:42:19,671
a place where the boy felt contented, free.

566
00:42:20,138 --> 00:42:22,748
A place he could be what he wanted te be.

567
00:42:25,109 --> 00:42:27,979
And what was inside there,
I'd say if 1 could.

568
00:42:28,446 --> 00:42:31,696
But up above, the Kangaroo
was up to ne goed.

569
00:42:40,158 --> 00:42:41,118
Can I come out now, Mom?

570
00:42:41,325 --> 00:42:43,134
No, Rudy. Stay in your room.

571
00:42:43,461 --> 00:42:45,361
-But, Mom...
-Stay inside.

572
00:42:57,308 --> 00:42:58,948
Mr. Vladikoff?

573
00:43:11,823 --> 00:43:13,283
Eating. Go.

574
00:43:13,591 --> 00:43:17,281
Yes, l realize you're busy,
but I need your help.

575
00:43:18,296 --> 00:43:19,466
It's Horton.

576
00:43:19,697 --> 00:43:22,127
He's become obsessed with a clover.

577
00:43:22,533 --> 00:43:25,663
And he actually thinks
there are little people on it.

578
00:43:28,506 --> 00:43:30,375
I want that clover destroyed.

579
00:43:30,708 --> 00:43:33,488
Sure. What a big deal this is for you, bro.

580
00:43:35,313 --> 00:43:39,703
I'd do it myself, but being a lady,
I prefer not to get my hands dirty.

581
00:43:40,952 --> 00:43:43,502
But I hear you have no problem with that.

582
00:43:45,223 --> 00:43:46,212
No.

583
00:43:46,824 --> 00:43:49,314
No problem. Easy peazy.

584
00:43:50,161 --> 00:43:53,261
But I will only do this for a price.

585
00:43:53,798 --> 00:43:56,227
In exchange for a brand new pair of...

586
00:43:57,235 --> 00:43:58,315
No.

587
00:43:59,170 --> 00:44:01,800
This little kangaroo.

588
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:05,549
-Mom!
-Quiet, Rudy. Mommy's thinking it over.

589
00:44:08,479 --> 00:44:10,558
Well, thanks, but on second thought,

590
00:44:10,915 --> 00:44:13,955
I think I'm going to have
the Wickersham brothers

591
00:44:14,485 --> 00:44:15,565
take care of this for me.

592
00:44:15,820 --> 00:44:18,370
Yeah, of course, Wickersham.
I mean, they're a classy operation.

593
00:44:18,823 --> 00:44:21,453
You know, they do... Wait! No!
You can't go with Wickersham!

594
00:44:21,893 --> 00:44:25,583
No, no, no, the Wickershams would
be perfect for this job.

595
00:44:26,197 --> 00:44:29,297
But they're monkeys! Is not scary!

596
00:44:29,834 --> 00:44:33,144
Thanks, anyway. Maybe next time.

597
00:44:33,704 --> 00:44:34,694
Wait!

598
00:44:35,339 --> 00:44:37,999
Here is what I will do to precious clover.

599
00:44:38,442 --> 00:44:41,372
I will take it, I will crush it,

600
00:44:41,879 --> 00:44:44,339
and I will devour it.

601
00:44:51,889 --> 00:44:53,119
Bigger than it look.

602
00:44:53,391 --> 00:44:54,621
One second.

603
00:44:56,761 --> 00:44:57,931
Holy moly.

604
00:44:59,463 --> 00:45:00,483
Hang on.

605
00:45:03,901 --> 00:45:05,481
Then I regurgitate it.

606
00:45:05,770 --> 00:45:09,080
Then I'm going to devour it second time!

607
00:45:09,774 --> 00:45:11,524
So, two times devoured.

608
00:45:12,476 --> 00:45:16,136
Sounds nice, but I think
I'll talk to the Wickershams.

609
00:45:16,948 --> 00:45:17,968
Wait!

610
00:45:19,283 --> 00:45:20,833
Here is best part.

611
00:45:21,118 --> 00:45:24,898
I do all gratis.

612
00:45:26,390 --> 00:45:27,879
That's free, bro.

613
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:30,450
What do you think?

614
00:45:33,497 --> 00:45:34,426
Deal.

615
00:45:34,632 --> 00:45:38,092
Yes! Score. Thanking you.
You won't regret.

616
00:46:14,538 --> 00:46:15,558
Mayor!

617
00:46:16,140 --> 00:46:17,279
Mayor!

618
00:46:17,508 --> 00:46:20,468
Open up, Mr. Mayor! Mr. Mayor!

619
00:46:22,313 --> 00:46:24,713
It's snowing! In the summer!

620
00:46:30,154 --> 00:46:32,084
Yes. Yes, it is.

621
00:46:32,456 --> 00:46:34,356
It's a dramatic change in the weather,

622
00:46:34,692 --> 00:46:36,972
as if we were a speck,
floating through space.

623
00:46:37,361 --> 00:46:40,611
I don't know how you knew,
but somehow you did,

624
00:46:41,165 --> 00:46:45,585
and Whoville is headed for disaster.

625
00:46:46,704 --> 00:46:48,194
Horton.

626
00:46:48,506 --> 00:46:49,435
What?

627
00:46:49,674 --> 00:46:51,314
Nothing. I'm on it.

628
00:46:51,642 --> 00:46:54,332
It's up to us to save
the people of Whoville.

629
00:46:58,649 --> 00:47:01,199
You're small, but there are a lot of you!

630
00:47:02,353 --> 00:47:03,583
That's it.

631
00:47:05,489 --> 00:47:07,009
Okay, anybody else?

632
00:47:07,992 --> 00:47:09,012
Good.

633
00:47:10,695 --> 00:47:14,235
No, no. No enjoyment. This is not fun.
It is a sign of doom!

634
00:47:16,701 --> 00:47:18,071
Aw, sweetie, that's...

635
00:47:18,369 --> 00:47:20,619
No, no, no! Danger! Danger!

636
00:47:23,374 --> 00:47:25,683
Stop having fun immediately!

637
00:47:26,077 --> 00:47:28,157
This is dangerous! Okay!

638
00:47:31,082 --> 00:47:32,192
Stop it!

639
00:47:39,957 --> 00:47:41,037
Horton!

640
00:47:49,433 --> 00:47:50,693
Hey, Mayor.

641
00:47:51,736 --> 00:47:52,906
We're in big trouble down here.

642
00:47:53,137 --> 00:47:55,597
It's happening!
It's snowing in the middle of summer.

643
00:47:56,073 --> 00:47:57,413
It's the end of the world!

644
00:48:01,112 --> 00:48:04,132
Hold on, Mayor.
I think I know what your problem is.

645
00:48:15,459 --> 00:48:17,038
There. That better?

646
00:48:19,497 --> 00:48:21,366
That seems to have worked.

647
00:48:23,234 --> 00:48:24,134
Do I smell peanuts?

648
00:48:24,335 --> 00:48:27,795
Yeah, they're my favorite snack,
but they tend to linger.

649
00:48:34,011 --> 00:48:35,000
Finwick, no!

650
00:48:36,781 --> 00:48:39,411
Hang on, Mr. Mayor.
I may have to put up a fight.

651
00:48:39,850 --> 00:48:41,870
A frightened elephant can be
very dangerous!

652
00:48:42,253 --> 00:48:45,623
All right!
You've called down the thunder, buddy!

653
00:48:46,157 --> 00:48:50,197
You hungry for trouble? I'm an
“All you can eat" salad bar! Take a bite!

654
00:48:54,098 --> 00:48:55,178
I hate running.

655
00:48:55,433 --> 00:48:56,633
Morton!

656
00:48:56,867 --> 00:48:58,887
Don't do that.

657
00:48:59,270 --> 00:49:00,350
Horton!

658
00:49:01,872 --> 00:49:03,832
Horton! There you are!

659
00:49:04,175 --> 00:49:06,395
We got trouble! Wait, stay, wait!
Did you hear that?

660
00:49:06,811 --> 00:49:11,381
No, I'm here, okay. Listen. No! Go!
Kangaroo has gone nuts, bananas.

661
00:49:12,116 --> 00:49:14,606
She's telling everyone that
you should be kicked out of Nool.

662
00:49:15,019 --> 00:49:17,448
She said that?
I thought we were her friends.

663
00:49:17,855 --> 00:49:19,725
Word is she's gone to Vlad!

664
00:49:20,057 --> 00:49:22,986
Vlad? Vlad? I know two Vlads.

665
00:49:23,494 --> 00:49:27,004
Is it the bad Vlad
or the bunny Vlad that makes the cookies?

666
00:49:27,565 --> 00:49:30,695
Yeah, Horton, she's sending you
a bunny with cookies.

667
00:49:31,202 --> 00:49:33,782
I think we can assume it's the bad Vlad.

668
00:49:34,371 --> 00:49:35,511
Yeah, that's a good call.

669
00:49:35,739 --> 00:49:40,219
So unless you're cool
with giant, razor-sharp claws

670
00:49:40,911 --> 00:49:44,191
ripping the flesh off your body,
I'd get rid of the clover!

671
00:49:44,715 --> 00:49:47,345
I can't! promised the Mayor.

672
00:49:48,252 --> 00:49:50,422
I meant what I said,
and I said what I meant,

673
00:49:50,821 --> 00:49:53,071
and an elephant's faithful, 100%.

674
00:49:53,491 --> 00:49:58,061
Please. For me, just this once.
Be faithful 99% of the time.

675
00:49:58,762 --> 00:50:02,662
I've never gotten 99% on anything,
and I think I'm awesome! So, come on!

676
00:50:03,267 --> 00:50:06,577
I meant what I said,
and I said what I meant.

677
00:50:07,605 --> 00:50:09,475
I'm not gonna say it.

678
00:50:09,840 --> 00:50:12,470
You can do that all day,
it's not happening.

679
00:50:13,511 --> 00:50:14,681
An elephant's faithful, 100%.

680
00:50:14,912 --> 00:50:19,011
That's right. That's my code, my motto.
But thanks for the warning.

681
00:50:20,017 --> 00:50:21,716
Motto. Okay.

682
00:50:22,052 --> 00:50:23,692
But watch the skies.

683
00:50:24,021 --> 00:50:26,831
Keep watching the skies!

684
00:50:31,795 --> 00:50:33,755
Mayor, you need to get
everyone underground.

685
00:50:34,098 --> 00:50:34,998
Now!

686
00:50:36,033 --> 00:50:37,553
1 don't want to sound the alarm,

687
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:39,648
but there's a good possibility
we may be attacked

688
00:50:39,970 --> 00:50:42,580
-by a giant carnivorous bird.
-What?

689
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:45,970
There's a small chance it could be a bunny
with cookies, but ! wouldn't count on it.

690
00:50:48,546 --> 00:50:49,806
They are formidable.

691
00:50:50,080 --> 00:50:51,830
Mayor? Are you there?

692
00:50:52,550 --> 00:50:55,180
Yeah. No. That's a great idea. It's just...

693
00:50:55,619 --> 00:50:59,309
In order to get everyone mobilized,
I'd need the okay of the City Council,

694
00:50:59,924 --> 00:51:02,174
and they never listen to me.

695
00:51:02,593 --> 00:51:04,373
I've been called a boob,

696
00:51:04,728 --> 00:51:06,398
several times. I can't do it!

697
00:51:06,830 --> 00:51:09,230
You have to talk to them, Mayor!
Okay. Listen.

698
00:51:12,002 --> 00:51:13,312
Bad Vlad!

699
00:51:13,604 --> 00:51:14,743
Bad Vlad!

700
00:51:15,506 --> 00:51:16,906
Bad Vlad!

701
00:51:24,181 --> 00:51:26,371
That is definitely not a bunny.

702
00:51:34,491 --> 00:51:38,241
Lost him. Meant to lose him,
and I lost him. Good.

703
00:51:44,101 --> 00:51:45,591
Is this tree for real? Come on!

704
00:51:45,869 --> 00:51:48,499
Hang on, Whoville!
This is gonna get rough!

705
00:51:59,883 --> 00:52:01,872
Now you're going to get it!

706
00:52:03,220 --> 00:52:04,970
Get ready for the best!

707
00:52:07,958 --> 00:52:09,328
Leave me alone!

708
00:52:14,632 --> 00:52:15,802
Horton!

709
00:52:27,711 --> 00:52:29,261
I just know he's gonna
jump out somewhere.

710
00:52:29,546 --> 00:52:30,596
Hello.

711
00:52:51,235 --> 00:52:52,495
Chess mate.

712
00:52:53,404 --> 00:52:55,484
Now it's time for me to take clover

713
00:52:55,873 --> 00:52:58,273
and crush all the little people on it,
who are saying...

714
00:52:58,742 --> 00:53:01,702
Sorry. This is where we get off.

715
00:53:05,616 --> 00:53:07,136
Right in the beak!

716
00:53:09,687 --> 00:53:12,087
Cool line. Usually I can't think
of those things till later.

717
00:53:13,123 --> 00:53:14,673
-Mayor?
-Horton.

718
00:53:15,292 --> 00:53:16,221
Are you okay?

719
00:53:22,733 --> 00:53:25,343
Well, more or less. What happened?
The bird?

720
00:53:26,136 --> 00:53:29,506
Yeah, it attacked me.
Mayor, your people are in danger.

721
00:53:31,875 --> 00:53:33,245
You know what? I'm gonna do it.

722
00:53:33,544 --> 00:53:36,413
I'm going to go out there
and tell them what is going on.

723
00:53:36,914 --> 00:53:38,814
Perfect. Now, quick. Get going.

724
00:53:45,089 --> 00:53:46,989
Hey! Mr. Mayor! Something's wrong!

725
00:53:47,324 --> 00:53:50,194
-My basement's in the attic.
-The Science Museum is history.

726
00:53:50,661 --> 00:53:54,031
-The lost and found is missing.
-What's going on, Mr. Mayor?

727
00:53:54,598 --> 00:53:56,648
I'm declaring a state of emergency!

728
00:53:57,000 --> 00:53:59,630
Don't worry! Don't worry!

729
00:54:00,104 --> 00:54:02,354
The Mayor is just being a moron.

730
00:54:02,773 --> 00:54:05,733
No, wait! Whoville is in terrible danger!

731
00:54:06,243 --> 00:54:09,673
Everyone needs to get down to the
underground storage area immediately.

732
00:54:10,247 --> 00:54:11,917
Fine! Fine!

733
00:54:12,249 --> 00:54:14,529
Let's do this democratically.

734
00:54:15,753 --> 00:54:18,823
Who wants the joy and glory and festivity

735
00:54:19,323 --> 00:54:22,573
of the Who-Centennial
to proceed as planned?

736
00:54:23,427 --> 00:54:25,037
Yeah!

737
00:54:25,763 --> 00:54:28,543
And who, like the Mayor,

738
00:54:28,999 --> 00:54:32,249
thinks it would be better
to spend the Who-Centennial

739
00:54:32,803 --> 00:54:35,763
in an underground storage area?

740
00:54:36,840 --> 00:54:38,150
Yeah!

741
00:54:39,943 --> 00:54:41,643
Wait! You've gotta listen to me!

742
00:54:41,979 --> 00:54:44,609
Our whole world could explode!

743
00:54:49,386 --> 00:54:51,196
Much more quickly!

744
00:54:52,055 --> 00:54:54,484
And our world wouldn't make that noise.

745
00:54:56,226 --> 00:54:58,806
The people have spoken, Mr. Mayor.

746
00:54:59,897 --> 00:55:03,116
You're finished. No one believes you.

