00:55:03,667 --> 00:55:05,537
No one supports you.

748
00:55:07,571 --> 00:55:09,411
Horton believes me.

749
00:55:09,740 --> 00:55:10,850
Horton?

750
00:55:12,309 --> 00:55:13,919
Who's Horton?

751
00:55:14,411 --> 00:55:19,451
Horton is a giant elephant in the sky!

752
00:55:21,018 --> 00:55:21,918
Don't bother looking, he's invisible.

753
00:55:22,152 --> 00:55:25,552
And he's the one risking his life
to get Whoville,

754
00:55:26,089 --> 00:55:30,249
which, by the way,
is a speck on a clover, to safety!

755
00:55:42,372 --> 00:55:43,662
I can prove it!

756
00:55:43,907 --> 00:55:46,537
Horton's voice comes out of this horn.

757
00:55:51,515 --> 00:55:52,415
Horton!

758
00:55:53,750 --> 00:55:56,620
I have all the Whos
gathered in town square!

759
00:55:57,087 --> 00:55:58,787
Let them know you're there!

760
00:56:00,023 --> 00:56:03,153
Gee. This is kind of
a high-pressure situation, then.

761
00:56:06,697 --> 00:56:09,067
Wow. l am really drawing a blank here.

762
00:56:09,466 --> 00:56:10,606
I know!

763
00:56:14,938 --> 00:56:16,048
Horton!

764
00:56:16,874 --> 00:56:18,573
Horton, we're waiting!

765
00:56:19,543 --> 00:56:21,533
Time to show everyone that you exist,

766
00:56:21,912 --> 00:56:25,692
and by extension, what a non-boob I am.

767
00:56:33,156 --> 00:56:34,266
Wait!

768
00:56:34,491 --> 00:56:38,831
Everyone, look at the wind.
What do you think that that means?

769
00:56:40,397 --> 00:56:41,657
It means...

770
00:56:41,932 --> 00:56:44,332
It means, obviously...

771
00:56:45,502 --> 00:56:48,282
Let the kite-flying race begin!

772
00:57:06,356 --> 00:57:08,526
What a burn on you, Horton!

773
00:58:06,316 --> 00:58:07,576
Brain freeze.

774
00:58:14,825 --> 00:58:18,285
Give me back my speck!

775
00:58:18,862 --> 00:58:20,442
Not this time, guy.

776
00:58:27,337 --> 00:58:32,197
lam so sorry that I let you down,
but this... This is bigger than me.

777
00:58:32,943 --> 00:58:35,723
Get the family together
and get somewhere safe.

778
00:58:36,747 --> 00:58:39,207
I will! l believe you.

779
00:58:45,555 --> 00:58:47,605
I've got you now, elephant.

780
00:58:49,860 --> 00:58:51,090
No, no, no!

781
00:59:03,273 --> 00:59:04,323
Oh, no!

782
00:59:32,302 --> 00:59:33,322
Mayor?

783
00:59:34,171 --> 00:59:35,481
Anybody there?

784
00:59:36,907 --> 00:59:37,927
Hello?

785
00:59:39,176 --> 00:59:40,286
Anyone?

786
00:59:41,278 --> 00:59:43,968
But clover by clover by clover, he found

787
00:59:44,448 --> 00:59:47,437
that the one he sought for
was just not around.

788
00:59:48,919 --> 00:59:49,939
Mayor?

789
00:59:52,189 --> 00:59:53,118
Hello?

790
00:59:53,323 --> 00:59:56,482
And by noon, poor Horton,
more dead than alive,

791
00:59:56,993 --> 01:00:00,773
had picked, searched and piled up 9,005.

792
01:00:02,299 --> 01:00:03,469
Hello?

793
01:00:04,468 --> 01:00:06,078
Sorry to bother you,

794
01:00:06,503 --> 01:00:07,673
nobody.

795
01:00:11,341 --> 01:00:12,651
Knock, knock.

796
01:00:14,277 --> 01:00:17,347
This is where you'd say, "Who's there?"

797
01:00:17,848 --> 01:00:20,658
if there were any Whos there.

798
01:00:22,686 --> 01:00:24,856
Get it? "Whos there.”

799
01:00:29,392 --> 01:00:32,321
All day he looked, looked on and on,

800
01:00:33,997 --> 01:00:36,216
until his hope was almost gone.

801
01:00:37,000 --> 01:00:39,630
No, no, no! Please, no!

802
01:00:41,238 --> 01:00:42,698
This isn't fair!

803
01:00:47,377 --> 01:00:49,717
But, wait, could this one be the one?

804
01:00:50,147 --> 01:00:52,547
Was all his searching finally done?

805
01:00:52,983 --> 01:00:55,383
Ah, yes, for this was the hour.

806
01:00:55,819 --> 01:00:58,659
Horton had found them
on the three millionth flower.

807
01:00:59,156 --> 01:01:01,266
Mayor! Mayor!

808
01:01:01,658 --> 01:01:03,298
I found you!

809
01:01:06,363 --> 01:01:07,533
Mayor?

810
01:01:08,064 --> 01:01:09,374
Are you there?

811
01:01:09,733 --> 01:01:10,843
Mayor?

812
01:01:15,005 --> 01:01:16,085
Mayor.

813
01:01:23,280 --> 01:01:24,950
Mayor, are you there?

814
01:01:28,218 --> 01:01:29,448
Mayor!

815
01:01:35,559 --> 01:01:36,489
Mayor?

816
01:01:39,429 --> 01:01:40,449
Mayor?

817
01:01:42,933 --> 01:01:45,543
Mayor!

818
01:01:53,910 --> 01:01:55,810
No, this is Floyd.

819
01:01:57,414 --> 01:01:59,024
Can I take a message?

820
01:02:03,153 --> 01:02:05,872
Mayor! You're okay!

821
01:02:08,758 --> 01:02:11,368
Horton! Horton! Stop! Stop it!

822
01:02:15,332 --> 01:02:16,321
Sorry.

823
01:02:16,566 --> 01:02:19,846
lt must have been rough down there.
l can't believe found you.

824
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:22,243
You really had me worried.

825
01:02:23,506 --> 01:02:25,556
Say! The Mayor was right!

826
01:02:25,942 --> 01:02:27,962
Daddy! Daddy! Daddy!

827
01:02:28,311 --> 01:02:31,031
Okay, I'm all right, and so are you.

828
01:02:36,920 --> 01:02:38,730
Citizens of Whoville!

829
01:02:41,124 --> 01:02:44,814
I'd like you to meet our friend Horton.

830
01:02:49,499 --> 01:02:51,198
He's going to help us!

831
01:02:53,970 --> 01:02:54,990
I've got this.

832
01:02:55,205 --> 01:02:57,194
This is the Chairman...

833
01:02:57,540 --> 01:02:58,500
Idiot!

834
01:02:58,708 --> 01:03:01,318
You're finished in this town!
Is that understood? Finished.

835
01:03:01,778 --> 01:03:03,147
You boob!

836
01:03:04,881 --> 01:03:06,580
I'm just joking.

837
01:03:11,388 --> 01:03:12,348
Good one.

838
01:03:12,555 --> 01:03:14,395
Horton, this is my wife Sally.

839
01:03:14,724 --> 01:03:15,864
You exist!

840
01:03:16,126 --> 01:03:18,236
This means my husband isn't crazy.

841
01:03:18,628 --> 01:03:19,998
Hooray!

842
01:03:20,297 --> 01:03:24,017
And a few of my daughters,
Haley, Holly, Hooly, Hilda and Hedy.

843
01:03:24,634 --> 01:03:25,654
-Hi!
-Hi!

844
01:03:25,869 --> 01:03:28,969
And here is Miss Yelp, my loyal assistant.

845
01:03:29,506 --> 01:03:31,816
-And here's Dr. Larue.
-You saved us!

846
01:03:32,208 --> 01:03:33,498
And Burt from accounting,

847
01:03:33,743 --> 01:03:36,143
and Mrs. MeGillicuddy, and Mr. Farfoogan

848
01:03:36,546 --> 01:03:38,245
from the Clugan Farfoogans,

849
01:03:38,548 --> 01:03:40,098
and the old man in the bathtub.

850
01:03:40,383 --> 01:03:41,933
Let's not overwhelm the poor fellow.

851
01:03:42,218 --> 01:03:43,768
He's never gonna remember
all these names.

852
01:03:44,054 --> 01:03:46,634
Well, I'll try my best.

853
01:03:47,924 --> 01:03:49,944
Sally, Chairman,

854
01:03:50,327 --> 01:03:52,257
Haley, Hooly, Holly, Hilda,
Hedy, Miss Yelp,

855
01:03:52,595 --> 01:03:55,174
Dr. Larue, Burt from accounting,
Mrs. McGillicuddy, Mr. Farfoogan

856
01:03:55,598 --> 01:03:59,258
of the Clugan Farfoogans,
and wasn't there an old guy in a shower?

857
01:03:59,869 --> 01:04:01,009
Bathtub.

858
01:04:01,237 --> 01:04:03,077
-Yeah!
-We're all here, Horton,

859
01:04:04,074 --> 01:04:07,264
and we all believe in you.

860
01:04:08,511 --> 01:04:10,291
Wow. That's awesome.

861
01:04:10,613 --> 01:04:13,102
And it's a responsibility
I do not take lightly.

862
01:04:13,550 --> 01:04:17,210
I promise you a future
that is safe, sound and stable.

863
01:04:17,787 --> 01:04:22,446
We will create a world where every Who
is endowed with three inalienable rights,

864
01:04:23,193 --> 01:04:24,593
to be determined at a later date.

865
01:04:26,229 --> 01:04:30,509
And we will put a speck on Mount Nool
before the end of this decade.

866
01:04:38,141 --> 01:04:40,751
This elephant is crazy! Oh, my goodness.

867
01:04:41,211 --> 01:04:44,461
I gotta tell everybody.
I need to get to the Kangaroo.

868
01:04:45,448 --> 01:04:47,587
Wait till they find out about...

869
01:04:48,251 --> 01:04:51,291
You should have been seeing me.
I really let elephant have it.

870
01:04:51,788 --> 01:04:55,978
I chase him, I torment him, I break him
into million little elephant pieces.

871
01:04:57,127 --> 01:05:00,527
It was thing of beauty, really.
My best work. Classic Vlad.

872
01:05:01,097 --> 01:05:02,087
And the clover?

873
01:05:02,298 --> 01:05:05,667
Clover is finished!
No way in million years Horton find it.

874
01:05:06,236 --> 01:05:09,516
Read my beak. Clover is gone forever.

875
01:05:15,478 --> 01:05:18,788
I just saw Horton,
and he is still talking to that clover!

876
01:05:23,253 --> 01:05:24,213
Idiot!

877
01:05:24,454 --> 01:05:28,584
Whoa! Come on, I'm your bro!
It's me you're talking to. We have history!

878
01:05:29,926 --> 01:05:32,616
Come on, let's not forget,
I did this for free!

879
01:05:33,963 --> 01:05:36,743
What is happening to the jungle of Nool?

880
01:05:37,667 --> 01:05:40,477
There once was a time
when people were people

881
01:05:40,970 --> 01:05:42,720
and specks were specks.

882
01:05:43,773 --> 01:05:47,313
Well, l say, “If you can't see it,
hear it or feel it,

883
01:05:47,877 --> 01:05:49,457
“it doesn't exist!"

884
01:05:50,547 --> 01:05:53,127
Our way of life is under attack!

885
01:05:53,550 --> 01:05:56,620
And who is leading that attack? Horton!

886
01:05:57,153 --> 01:05:59,462
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

887
01:05:59,856 --> 01:06:01,936
Wait a minute!
This is Horton we're talking about.

888
01:06:02,325 --> 01:06:04,935
You all know him, he wouldn't hurt a fly.

889
01:06:05,361 --> 01:06:09,111
Except for that fly city he sat on.
But he didn't do that on purpose.

890
01:06:09,699 --> 01:06:11,099
Shut up, mouse!

891
01:06:12,202 --> 01:06:15,572
That's weird. My brownies are burning.
I gotta go!

892
01:06:17,207 --> 01:06:22,007
Are we going to let troublemakers like
Horton poison the minds of our children?

893
01:06:22,745 --> 01:06:24,325
Not the children!

894
01:06:25,181 --> 01:06:29,311
When Horton tells our children
about worlds beyond the jungle,

895
01:06:29,986 --> 01:06:31,946
he makes them question authority!

896
01:06:32,322 --> 01:06:35,862
Which leads to defiance!
Which leads to anarchy!

897
01:06:36,426 --> 01:06:38,616
Yeah! Horton must pay!

898
01:06:39,028 --> 01:06:40,317
It's that speck!

899
01:06:40,563 --> 01:06:42,203
We have to do something!

900
01:06:42,532 --> 01:06:43,702
For the children!

901
01:06:43,933 --> 01:06:45,163
For the children!

902
01:06:45,401 --> 01:06:49,741
Are we going to let him
get away with this?

903
01:06:50,406 --> 01:06:52,186
No!

904
01:06:52,675 --> 01:06:54,195
Let's go!

905
01:07:17,967 --> 01:07:21,037
Morton! I told you! 100%!

906
01:07:22,138 --> 01:07:23,127
Horton!

907
01:07:23,373 --> 01:07:25,483
Morton, pick up your feet! Jeez.

908
01:07:25,875 --> 01:07:27,215
It's not me!

909
01:07:29,379 --> 01:07:32,689
I see. It's an angry mob. Sorry, Morton.

910
01:07:33,249 --> 01:07:35,359
I thought it was you
that was making all the...

911
01:07:35,752 --> 01:07:36,982
But it's...

912
01:07:37,487 --> 01:07:38,717
Oh, darn.

913
01:07:40,390 --> 01:07:41,700
Run, Horton!

914
01:07:42,792 --> 01:07:44,102
There he is!

915
01:07:45,495 --> 01:07:46,725
Let's rope him!

916
01:07:46,963 --> 01:07:48,393
Let's cage him!

917
01:07:49,966 --> 01:07:52,625
No! No! No!

918
01:07:56,506 --> 01:07:57,935
Stop!

919
01:07:59,576 --> 01:08:01,476
Hey, fellas. Good to see you,

920
01:08:01,811 --> 01:08:03,071
all at once.

921
01:08:03,513 --> 01:08:04,803
You look really great as a horde.

922
01:08:05,081 --> 01:08:06,831
Horton, Horton, Horton,

923
01:08:07,150 --> 01:08:10,400
look at the mess
you've created for yourself.

924
01:08:10,954 --> 01:08:14,234
All this hullabaloo over a silly little flower.

925
01:08:15,258 --> 01:08:16,598
It's a speck.

926
01:08:17,260 --> 01:08:21,450
Right. mean, it's silly, really,
all this talk of roping you,

927
01:08:22,131 --> 01:08:25,971
and caging you, and, well,
we don't need to go into the details.

928
01:08:26,603 --> 01:08:31,082
The point is, this angry mob,
all the trouble you're in,

929
01:08:31,808 --> 01:08:33,587
it can all go away.

930
01:08:36,179 --> 01:08:38,669
-Really?
-Of course.

931
01:08:39,482 --> 01:08:43,992
All you have to do is admit to everyone
that there are no little people

932
01:08:44,687 --> 01:08:46,296
living on that speck.

933
01:08:46,622 --> 01:08:49,643
That you were wrong and I was right.

934
01:08:51,194 --> 01:08:55,764
You do that and things can go right back
to the way they were.

935
01:08:57,033 --> 01:09:02,573
But if you don't, you're going to
have to pay the price.

936
01:09:11,014 --> 01:09:13,354
So, I just have to say it isn't true?

937
01:09:18,854 --> 01:09:22,484
Go ahead. Rope me, cage me.
Do whatever you want.

938
01:09:23,426 --> 01:09:25,176
But there are people on this speck.

939
01:09:25,528 --> 01:09:29,478
And they have a Mayor, who has
96 daughters and one son named JoJo,

940
01:09:30,099 --> 01:09:32,788
who all share a bathroom,
whatever that is,

941
01:09:34,504 --> 01:09:37,604
and even though you can't hear
or see them at all,

942
01:09:38,107 --> 01:09:41,037
a person's a person, no matter how small.

943
01:09:48,451 --> 01:09:50,941
That was beautiful, Horton.

944
01:09:51,754 --> 01:09:53,394
Rope him! Cage him!

945
01:09:53,723 --> 01:09:57,443
And burn that speck
in a pot of boiling Beezlenut oil!

946
01:10:02,365 --> 01:10:04,144
They don't believe we're here.

947
01:10:04,467 --> 01:10:06,366
We've got to make some noise!

948
01:10:06,736 --> 01:10:08,696
We are here! We are here! We are here!

949
01:10:09,072 --> 01:10:10,942
We are here! We are here! We are here!

950
01:10:11,274 --> 01:10:12,704
We are here! We are here! We are here!

951
01:10:12,975 --> 01:10:14,235
Come on!

952
01:10:14,944 --> 01:10:17,164
-Everybody!
-We are here! We are here! We are here!

953
01:10:17,580 --> 01:10:19,510
We are here! We are here! We are here!

954
01:10:28,291 --> 01:10:31,801
This will teach you not to make up stories
about people on specks!

955
01:10:32,395 --> 01:10:34,475
Listen! There they are!

956
01:10:38,668 --> 01:10:40,277
-Rope him.
-Cage him!

957
01:10:41,070 --> 01:10:42,530
It's not working.

958
01:10:43,072 --> 01:10:45,212
I can hear you,
but their ears aren't strong enough.

959
01:10:45,608 --> 01:10:47,068
We need to be louder!

960
01:10:47,343 --> 01:10:50,093
Get every Who to make noise! Everyone!

961
01:10:50,580 --> 01:10:53,740
We are here! We are here! We are here!

962
01:10:54,283 --> 01:10:56,153
JoJo! Where are you going?

963
01:10:56,586 --> 01:10:59,306
We need every voice! JoJo!

964
01:11:03,192 --> 01:11:07,002
You need to make some noise down there,
or we'll all be destroyed!

965
01:11:08,364 --> 01:11:11,384
The Mayor grabbed a tom-tom
and started to smack it,

966
01:11:13,035 --> 01:11:15,934
and all over Whoville,
they whooped up a racket.

967
01:11:18,508 --> 01:11:20,848
They rattled tin kettles!
They beat on brass pans!

968
01:11:21,277 --> 01:11:23,467
On garbage pail tops
and old cranberry cans!

969
01:11:23,846 --> 01:11:26,455
They blew on bazookas
and blasted great teats.

970
01:11:26,883 --> 01:11:29,903
On clarinets, oompahs,
and boompahs, and flutes!

971
01:11:33,122 --> 01:11:34,172
There!

972
01:11:36,359 --> 01:11:37,619
Can they hear us now?

973
01:11:38,327 --> 01:11:41,957
Listen, please.
It's the most beautiful thing ever.

974
01:11:42,532 --> 01:11:44,172
I don't hear nothing!

975
01:11:44,867 --> 01:11:47,147
I don't think so. But keep trying.

976
01:11:48,671 --> 01:11:50,281
I'll never give in!

977
01:11:54,644 --> 01:11:58,244
Are you sure that every Who down
in Whoville is trying?

978
01:12:05,788 --> 01:12:07,048
We are here! We are here!

979
01:12:07,323 --> 01:12:08,663
Where's JoJo?

980
01:12:08,925 --> 01:12:11,035
Probably at the old observatory.

981
01:12:24,874 --> 01:12:26,483
Hey! There's a limit!

982
01:12:34,016 --> 01:12:36,536
That's not supposed to stretch that far!

983
01:12:46,395 --> 01:12:47,565
JoJo!

984
01:12:48,231 --> 01:12:49,571
You built this?

985
01:13:40,249 --> 01:13:43,318
We are here! We are here! We are here!

986
01:13:43,819 --> 01:13:46,569
We are here! We are here! We are here!

987
01:13:48,491 --> 01:13:51,651
We are here! We are here! We are here!

988
01:13:58,534 --> 01:14:00,704
You're making a mistake.

989
01:14:03,306 --> 01:14:04,236
But, Mom!

990
01:14:04,473 --> 01:14:06,963
This doesn't concern you, sweetie.
Back in your pouch!

991
01:14:12,949 --> 01:14:14,619
Everybody! Don't stop!

992
01:14:17,620 --> 01:14:19,730
Keep going! This is gonna do it!

993
01:14:20,122 --> 01:14:23,932
We are here! We are here! We are here!

994
01:14:24,527 --> 01:14:25,547
Can they hear?

995
01:14:25,795 --> 01:14:26,755
No!

996
01:14:35,538 --> 01:14:38,727
No matter what happens,
I couldn't ask for a better son.

997
01:14:42,845 --> 01:14:44,305
Hey, JoJo!

998
01:14:45,147 --> 01:14:47,047
Come on! Keep going!

999
01:14:52,188 --> 01:14:53,648
No!

1000
01:14:58,828 --> 01:15:01,988
We are here! We are here! We are here!

1001
01:15:06,102 --> 01:15:07,062
No!

